1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:03,240
ALL DEPICTED EVENTS ARE FICTIONAL

2
00:00:17,040 --> 00:00:18,720
Your faculty is hosting a jazz showcase.

3
00:00:18,800 --> 00:00:21,320
My friends want me to sing,
but I don't want to.

4
00:00:21,880 --> 00:00:23,800
I'll be there in the crowd.

5
00:00:23,880 --> 00:00:25,960
I'll be in the very front row,

6
00:00:26,960 --> 00:00:28,400
the very same spot I fell for you.

7
00:00:28,480 --> 00:00:29,960
I want to ask you one question.

8
00:00:30,040 --> 00:00:31,600
How about we start dating?

9
00:00:31,680 --> 00:00:33,480
<i>I never gave up on you, you know?</i>

10
00:00:34,120 --> 00:00:35,440
But when I'm with you,

11
00:00:35,520 --> 00:00:37,720
<i>it feels like someone else has your heart.</i>

12
00:00:40,040 --> 00:00:41,000
I choose you.

13
00:00:41,080 --> 00:00:43,400
<i>You're not the only one</i>
<i>who feels this way.</i>

14
00:00:43,480 --> 00:00:45,520
<i>Now I feel the same way about you</i>

15
00:00:45,600 --> 00:00:46,960
<i>as you do about me.</i>

16
00:00:49,240 --> 00:00:52,080
As for the large-scale artwork
for the jazz showcase…

17
00:00:53,040 --> 00:00:53,880
Yes?

18
00:00:53,960 --> 00:00:55,600
This is for the College of Music?

19
00:00:55,680 --> 00:00:56,960
Correct!

20
00:00:57,760 --> 00:01:00,560
So that means I'm kind of part of
this showcase with him.

21
00:01:01,240 --> 00:01:02,240
Something like that.

22
00:01:02,960 --> 00:01:05,480
It's rare that the music students
ask for our help,

23
00:01:05,560 --> 00:01:07,560
so we have to do our best.

24
00:01:07,640 --> 00:01:10,720
Therefore, we're gonna pick a leader
and dive right in.

25
00:01:11,920 --> 00:01:12,840
Duang, you do it.

26
00:01:12,920 --> 00:01:14,920
- No way.
- What?

27
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:16,720
Qin's part of the showcase.

28
00:01:16,800 --> 00:01:19,080
If I'm the leader,
I won't get to see him at all.

29
00:01:19,600 --> 00:01:21,320
Jeez, you're so whiny.

30
00:01:22,160 --> 00:01:23,640
Right, whoever wants to lead,

31
00:01:23,720 --> 00:01:24,640
step up to the front.

32
00:01:38,120 --> 00:01:39,040
What…

33
00:02:08,639 --> 00:02:09,759
Wow!

34
00:02:09,840 --> 00:02:11,640
Duang, you want to be the leader?

35
00:02:14,280 --> 00:02:16,480
Go on, Duang. You're amazing.

36
00:02:16,560 --> 00:02:17,800
All right,

37
00:02:17,880 --> 00:02:20,360
so it's settled. Duang's the leader.

38
00:02:21,320 --> 00:02:23,280
I barely have any time though.

39
00:02:23,360 --> 00:02:25,280
It won't take long.
Only two to three days.

40
00:02:25,360 --> 00:02:27,640
Bro, you need to do it.

41
00:02:27,720 --> 00:02:29,840
Qin's gonna get to see
you shine, you know?

42
00:02:31,120 --> 00:02:33,600
True, I wouldn't want it
to be anyone else.

43
00:02:33,680 --> 00:02:35,240
- True!
- True

44
00:02:35,320 --> 00:02:37,400
Give it up for our new leader!

45
00:02:40,680 --> 00:02:42,480
Duang, you're the best.

46
00:04:22,520 --> 00:04:23,520
Jeez,

47
00:04:24,400 --> 00:04:26,080
you're not letting me get my Qin energy.

48
00:04:27,200 --> 00:04:28,680
I can wipe it off myself.

49
00:04:32,320 --> 00:04:34,840
After tonight, I'll be really busy.

50
00:04:34,920 --> 00:04:37,600
I won't be able to see you for a few days.

51
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:41,880
Qin…

52
00:04:43,120 --> 00:04:45,400
What am I gonna do?

53
00:04:45,480 --> 00:04:47,520
I'll probably miss you so much

54
00:04:47,600 --> 00:04:49,840
that I'll die for sure.

55
00:04:51,040 --> 00:04:52,040
Why are you whining?

56
00:04:54,160 --> 00:04:56,720
Well, I'm not gonna see you at all.

57
00:04:59,640 --> 00:05:01,200
But whatever you draw

58
00:05:01,280 --> 00:05:03,560
will stand behind me when I'm onstage.

59
00:05:04,600 --> 00:05:06,520
Plus, I have my practice too.

60
00:05:12,880 --> 00:05:13,880
Yeah, you're right.

61
00:05:15,240 --> 00:05:16,800
Then I'll work so hard

62
00:05:16,880 --> 00:05:19,000
that my artwork will drop jaws!

63
00:05:20,120 --> 00:05:21,120
Who are you talking to?

64
00:05:22,920 --> 00:05:24,520
Let's just eat our cake.

65
00:05:24,600 --> 00:05:26,000
Come on.

66
00:05:30,840 --> 00:05:32,000
Big bite.

67
00:05:34,320 --> 00:05:35,160
You're adorable.

68
00:05:35,240 --> 00:05:37,280
Can you stop being so cute?

69
00:05:40,520 --> 00:05:41,960
I forgot.

70
00:05:42,040 --> 00:05:43,400
You can't stop it

71
00:05:43,480 --> 00:05:46,160
since it's the way you are.

72
00:05:46,680 --> 00:05:49,200
Big bite.

73
00:05:59,000 --> 00:05:59,840
Give me that.

74
00:06:00,760 --> 00:06:01,760
I can feed myself.

75
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:25,160
You want a bite?

76
00:06:30,880 --> 00:06:32,280
Fine, I'll feed myself.

77
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:45,640
Few, View, help Jamie scrub that off

78
00:06:45,720 --> 00:06:47,720
since that one barely shows up to class.

79
00:06:47,800 --> 00:06:49,720
His brain's not really braining.

80
00:06:50,560 --> 00:06:51,720
Just kidding.

81
00:06:52,480 --> 00:06:53,680
The rest of you, come here.

82
00:06:53,760 --> 00:06:54,640
So…

83
00:06:54,720 --> 00:06:56,600
I think we should have
a little meeting here.

84
00:06:56,680 --> 00:06:58,080
We'll to divide into groups.

85
00:06:58,160 --> 00:06:59,440
Please help Pae.

86
00:06:59,520 --> 00:07:02,480
We'll make some multi-faceted boxes.

87
00:07:02,560 --> 00:07:04,480
I think I'll handle this one.

88
00:07:04,560 --> 00:07:06,440
All right, go ahead and divide up the work

89
00:07:06,520 --> 00:07:08,160
since this is gonna be…

90
00:07:09,480 --> 00:07:10,360
View.

91
00:07:10,960 --> 00:07:12,640
I'm gonna take a quick bathroom break.

92
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:14,880
Take care of this for me.

93
00:07:23,960 --> 00:07:26,280
<i>Are you at your condo? Can I come over?</i>

94
00:07:30,040 --> 00:07:31,800
<i>Of course.</i>

95
00:07:50,080 --> 00:07:50,960
GOOD LUCK AT PRACTICE

96
00:07:51,040 --> 00:07:51,960
TEXT ME IF YOU MISS ME

97
00:07:52,040 --> 00:07:53,400
<i>Practice will run late tonight.</i>

98
00:08:09,640 --> 00:08:10,560
Here.

99
00:08:23,800 --> 00:08:25,720
What do we have here, my friend?

100
00:08:26,600 --> 00:08:27,920
Right,

101
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:28,960
I got it.

102
00:08:29,640 --> 00:08:31,600
Duang's been pulled away, huh?

103
00:08:35,440 --> 00:08:36,679
He's busy working.

104
00:08:37,240 --> 00:08:38,360
He's got a lot to do.

105
00:08:39,559 --> 00:08:40,400
So how does it feel

106
00:08:40,480 --> 00:08:42,039
to be the one waiting?

107
00:08:42,120 --> 00:08:43,000
Tormenting?

108
00:08:49,880 --> 00:08:51,320
Hey, what's up?

109
00:08:52,960 --> 00:08:54,120
What are you talking about?

110
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:57,480
Someone here is realizing
how torturous it is to wait.

111
00:08:59,880 --> 00:09:00,760
The heck do you mean?

112
00:09:00,840 --> 00:09:01,920
Hey, wait.

113
00:09:03,600 --> 00:09:04,960
Time to rehearse.

114
00:09:19,240 --> 00:09:20,360
Ready?

115
00:09:29,840 --> 00:09:32,600
<i>It was meant to be</i>

116
00:09:33,880 --> 00:09:37,360
<i>Can't you see</i>

117
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:06,840
Boo!

118
00:10:09,040 --> 00:10:10,040
Hey,

119
00:10:10,120 --> 00:10:11,160
it's dark outside.

120
00:10:11,240 --> 00:10:12,080
Let's go eat.

121
00:10:12,160 --> 00:10:13,640
Okay.

122
00:10:14,320 --> 00:10:15,960
Any nice places to eat around here?

123
00:10:17,720 --> 00:10:18,840
What are you craving?

124
00:10:18,920 --> 00:10:20,080
Anything is fine.

125
00:10:21,120 --> 00:10:22,360
Give me some recommendations.

126
00:10:23,480 --> 00:10:25,480
I don't know that many restaurants.

127
00:10:25,560 --> 00:10:26,800
I'm more familiar with bars.

128
00:10:27,720 --> 00:10:29,240
I can tell!

129
00:10:29,320 --> 00:10:32,720
All my seniors are talking about you.

130
00:10:32,800 --> 00:10:34,960
Cutie this, cutie that.

131
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:36,920
That much?

132
00:10:37,880 --> 00:10:39,320
Don't act so surprised.

133
00:10:56,640 --> 00:10:58,040
Hey…

134
00:10:58,120 --> 00:11:00,000
can we not eat near the university?

135
00:11:00,920 --> 00:11:02,240
I don't want to see my friends.

136
00:11:03,080 --> 00:11:05,120
Wait, isn't that a good thing?

137
00:11:07,360 --> 00:11:08,600
Well, I bailed on them.

138
00:11:08,680 --> 00:11:10,680
I ditched work for you.

139
00:11:10,760 --> 00:11:12,640
They're gonna tease me.

140
00:11:12,720 --> 00:11:14,520
They don't want me
to be in a relationship.

141
00:11:16,640 --> 00:11:18,840
Is it bad that everyone says

142
00:11:19,640 --> 00:11:20,880
you're my boyfriend?

143
00:11:23,520 --> 00:11:25,600
Well… it's not like that.

144
00:11:25,680 --> 00:11:27,840
But we're not boyfriends.

145
00:11:29,880 --> 00:11:30,880
Who says?

146
00:11:31,720 --> 00:11:33,240
Marvis.

147
00:11:34,160 --> 00:11:35,680
I know that.

148
00:11:36,120 --> 00:11:37,120
I'm not falling in love.

149
00:11:37,200 --> 00:11:38,680
Alrighty,

150
00:11:38,760 --> 00:11:40,600
me neither.

151
00:11:52,440 --> 00:11:54,240
- That's it for me.
- Sure thing.

152
00:11:57,000 --> 00:11:58,600
What drink is this?

153
00:11:58,680 --> 00:11:59,680
I really can't read it.

154
00:12:01,120 --> 00:12:02,320
Chrysanthemum tea.

155
00:12:03,400 --> 00:12:04,640
Mum…

156
00:12:04,720 --> 00:12:06,000
Like mommy?

157
00:12:07,760 --> 00:12:10,160
No. Don't just mix up words.

158
00:12:10,240 --> 00:12:12,920
It's the name of a Thai herbal tea.

159
00:12:17,560 --> 00:12:18,600
I'll get iced pink milk.

160
00:12:20,760 --> 00:12:22,560
Look at you,

161
00:12:23,280 --> 00:12:24,480
asking questions,

162
00:12:24,560 --> 00:12:25,960
yet still playing it safe.

163
00:12:26,680 --> 00:12:27,960
I don't know if I'll like it.

164
00:12:28,040 --> 00:12:30,920
If not, you can trade with mine.

165
00:12:32,840 --> 00:12:34,360
Then, we'll get

166
00:12:34,440 --> 00:12:36,760
a chrysanthemum tea and an iced pink milk.

167
00:12:36,840 --> 00:12:38,200
- Of course.
- Thank you.

168
00:12:48,840 --> 00:12:49,880
Excuse me,

169
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:52,920
are you guys a couple?

170
00:12:58,280 --> 00:12:59,920
Do you want something?

171
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:02,120
If you're not a couple,

172
00:13:03,240 --> 00:13:04,720
can I get your Instagram?

173
00:13:07,320 --> 00:13:08,560
Oopsie…

174
00:13:09,160 --> 00:13:10,080
My bad.

175
00:13:13,880 --> 00:13:15,640
We're not a couple.

176
00:13:15,720 --> 00:13:18,040
Nope, we're not.

177
00:13:20,120 --> 00:13:21,840
But I won't give you my Instagram.

178
00:13:33,200 --> 00:13:34,120
All right.

179
00:13:54,920 --> 00:13:57,440
The color is uncanny.

180
00:13:57,520 --> 00:13:59,760
It's so yellow that it hurts your eyes.

181
00:13:59,840 --> 00:14:01,760
Why would it hurt my eyes?

182
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:05,080
Never mind.

183
00:14:05,600 --> 00:14:06,600
Want a sip?

184
00:14:25,960 --> 00:14:26,880
It's good, isn't it?

185
00:14:26,960 --> 00:14:29,440
It's very sweet,

186
00:14:30,400 --> 00:14:31,520
but I'm into it.

187
00:14:34,480 --> 00:14:35,400
I knew it.

188
00:14:45,280 --> 00:14:47,320
Good thing you didn't
give him your Instagram.

189
00:14:47,400 --> 00:14:49,280
He looks like a player.

190
00:14:49,360 --> 00:14:50,680
He doesn't make the cut.

191
00:14:53,560 --> 00:14:54,960
I just don't like him.

192
00:14:55,040 --> 00:14:56,280
He looks like a player.

193
00:14:56,360 --> 00:14:57,720
Even I can tell.

194
00:14:58,360 --> 00:14:59,840
It's not a big deal.

195
00:14:59,920 --> 00:15:01,680
It's not gonna be serious.

196
00:15:02,920 --> 00:15:03,760
It's kind of is.

197
00:15:04,200 --> 00:15:05,200
He's not making the cut.

198
00:15:05,280 --> 00:15:06,640
It's a no from me.

199
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:09,200
Then who's gonna make it?

200
00:15:12,200 --> 00:15:13,480
No one.

201
00:15:15,160 --> 00:15:16,720
Possessive much?

202
00:15:21,480 --> 00:15:23,160
What? Just gonna go silent?

203
00:15:23,240 --> 00:15:24,920
I'm not possessive.

204
00:15:26,280 --> 00:15:27,520
I got it.

205
00:15:28,720 --> 00:15:30,840
It's called being protective.

206
00:15:32,040 --> 00:15:33,400
Okay…

207
00:15:33,920 --> 00:15:35,920
Whatever you say.

208
00:16:07,240 --> 00:16:08,400
Pae,

209
00:16:08,480 --> 00:16:10,000
make it nice and smooth

210
00:16:10,080 --> 00:16:12,080
- so that it can be drawn on beautifully.
- I know.

211
00:16:12,160 --> 00:16:13,160
- Good.
- Jeez…

212
00:16:13,240 --> 00:16:14,720
I shouldn't've made you leader.

213
00:16:16,240 --> 00:16:17,200
Friends…

214
00:16:17,280 --> 00:16:18,440
Proad and Prach,

215
00:16:18,520 --> 00:16:19,760
do you mind speeding up?

216
00:16:19,840 --> 00:16:20,800
- Sure.
- Thank you.

217
00:16:23,280 --> 00:16:25,160
Whoa, friends!
Tew, my friend.

218
00:16:25,240 --> 00:16:28,600
You need a saxophone and some stars on it.

219
00:16:28,680 --> 00:16:29,800
Right, thank you so much.

220
00:16:32,600 --> 00:16:33,840
Aom,

221
00:16:33,920 --> 00:16:35,440
that's the cutest.

222
00:16:35,520 --> 00:16:37,600
- Amazing job.
- Come here.

223
00:16:38,800 --> 00:16:41,200
Why did you do that?
I need to finish my work!

224
00:16:41,280 --> 00:16:42,520
Unfinished work is one thing,

225
00:16:42,600 --> 00:16:44,280
you constantly walking around
is another!

226
00:16:44,360 --> 00:16:46,360
Look, you're giving me a headache.

227
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:49,800
Wait, I have that inhaler.

228
00:16:50,360 --> 00:16:51,520
Here.

229
00:16:51,600 --> 00:16:52,880
Look.

230
00:16:58,600 --> 00:17:00,800
Cute and practical.

231
00:17:00,880 --> 00:17:03,200
Everyone and their mother has one.

232
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:07,760
Get this, you can do this with them.

233
00:17:08,760 --> 00:17:09,720
Look.

234
00:17:13,800 --> 00:17:18,079
Inhalers assembled into lightning
from Dumble Inhaler V2!

235
00:17:18,160 --> 00:17:19,040
Hold up.

236
00:17:19,119 --> 00:17:20,680
I didn't pull you aside for this.

237
00:17:20,760 --> 00:17:22,680
You've got to chill the fuck out.

238
00:17:22,760 --> 00:17:24,119
The work is not that urgent.

239
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:27,040
But it is urgent!

240
00:17:27,119 --> 00:17:29,040
Urgent, my ass.
There are still two days left.

241
00:17:29,680 --> 00:17:30,560
Come on now,

242
00:17:30,640 --> 00:17:32,160
just get it done tonight.

243
00:17:32,240 --> 00:17:33,080
And don't slack off.

244
00:17:33,160 --> 00:17:34,560
Come help Pae and me over there.

245
00:17:35,600 --> 00:17:36,520
I'm off.

246
00:17:37,080 --> 00:17:39,000
Are you a superhuman?

247
00:17:39,080 --> 00:17:40,000
You're going to crash.

248
00:17:40,080 --> 00:17:41,600
Whatever. Are you going to help?

249
00:17:41,680 --> 00:17:42,720
Fine!

250
00:17:44,400 --> 00:17:45,720
Wait…

251
00:17:45,800 --> 00:17:47,280
Bastard, you took my inhaler!

252
00:17:47,360 --> 00:17:49,200
Duang!

253
00:17:50,400 --> 00:17:51,840
- Give it to me.
- Here.

254
00:18:25,920 --> 00:18:26,840
Pae,

255
00:18:27,360 --> 00:18:28,360
look at Duang.

256
00:18:30,280 --> 00:18:32,320
Goddammit, he's rushing it.

257
00:18:39,040 --> 00:18:40,800
Whoa! Duang, stop.

258
00:18:42,120 --> 00:18:44,480
If you paint with that brush,
you'll have to redo it.

259
00:18:46,080 --> 00:18:47,160
What?

260
00:18:47,800 --> 00:18:49,040
Right, my bad.

261
00:18:49,120 --> 00:18:50,520
I didn't look.

262
00:19:03,880 --> 00:19:06,160
JETNOTYET_ IS CALLING YOU

263
00:19:08,920 --> 00:19:09,800
Hello?

264
00:19:11,320 --> 00:19:13,040
<i>Sorry to bother you,</i>

265
00:19:13,120 --> 00:19:14,800
<i>but you need to check on Duang.</i>

266
00:19:15,960 --> 00:19:17,720
He's listening to literally no one.

267
00:19:17,800 --> 00:19:18,920
He's in low-battery mode.

268
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:20,160
Please make him sleep.

269
00:19:20,240 --> 00:19:21,960
<i>I'm begging you.</i>

270
00:19:22,040 --> 00:19:23,040
What's going on?

271
00:19:23,920 --> 00:19:25,760
<i>He's being stubborn</i>
<i>and pushing his limits.</i>

272
00:19:25,840 --> 00:19:27,240
<i>I'm afraid he's gonna drop dead.</i>

273
00:19:27,320 --> 00:19:28,640
<i>What's he doing?</i>

274
00:19:29,920 --> 00:19:31,920
Giving orders and helping friends.

275
00:19:32,000 --> 00:19:33,480
<i>He was drawing outlines at first,</i>

276
00:19:33,560 --> 00:19:35,080
<i>but he's doing everything now.</i>

277
00:19:35,160 --> 00:19:36,640
<i>Please put him to bed.</i>

278
00:19:36,720 --> 00:19:38,040
Where are you? I'm on my way.

279
00:19:38,720 --> 00:19:40,160
<i>In front of the faculty building.</i>

280
00:19:40,240 --> 00:19:43,040
<i>But the artwork is almost done</i>
<i>because he's rushing everything.</i>

281
00:19:43,120 --> 00:19:44,280
<i>He doesn't know his limits.</i>

282
00:20:06,800 --> 00:20:07,960
Duang, stop right there.

283
00:20:09,320 --> 00:20:10,920
You've had too much caffeine already.

284
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:13,480
Yeah, does your dad
own a coffee plantation?

285
00:20:13,560 --> 00:20:15,200
It's none of your business!

286
00:20:15,280 --> 00:20:17,280
I can drink as much coffee I want.

287
00:20:36,280 --> 00:20:37,760
You're still here!

288
00:20:40,920 --> 00:20:43,360
I'm not imagining things, am I?

289
00:20:43,440 --> 00:20:44,600
Is this real?

290
00:20:45,240 --> 00:20:46,160
It's real.

291
00:20:46,960 --> 00:20:48,240
I've missed you so much.

292
00:20:48,320 --> 00:20:50,680
I'm so happy you came to see me.

293
00:20:53,960 --> 00:20:55,640
How much coffee did you have?

294
00:20:59,800 --> 00:21:01,480
Aren't you afraid you'll go into shock?

295
00:21:02,720 --> 00:21:05,120
- You're worried about me--
- Eat.

296
00:21:06,440 --> 00:21:08,560
- But my work is--
- Go eat,

297
00:21:09,200 --> 00:21:10,520
or go back to the condo.

298
00:21:13,400 --> 00:21:14,520
Eating is fine.

299
00:21:28,840 --> 00:21:30,400
Finally, we can rest.

300
00:21:30,480 --> 00:21:32,480
Off he goes.

301
00:21:39,320 --> 00:21:41,520
Do you think it's okay to work like this?

302
00:21:42,400 --> 00:21:43,760
Why push yourself so hard?

303
00:21:44,440 --> 00:21:47,360
I just want to get things done quickly

304
00:21:47,440 --> 00:21:49,000
so that I can see you.

305
00:21:50,720 --> 00:21:51,920
Are you kidding me?

306
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:54,560
Do you know your limits?

307
00:21:56,320 --> 00:21:58,600
When I have to pull an all-nighter,
I do it at my place

308
00:21:58,680 --> 00:22:00,080
so I can fall asleep whenever.

309
00:22:01,240 --> 00:22:02,120
But this…

310
00:22:02,200 --> 00:22:03,800
What if you collapse?

311
00:22:08,200 --> 00:22:09,640
Do you think it makes me happy

312
00:22:10,720 --> 00:22:12,160
to see you sick?

313
00:22:20,080 --> 00:22:21,120
What are you smiling at?

314
00:22:24,360 --> 00:22:25,280
Well…

315
00:22:27,240 --> 00:22:29,280
Just stop being so cute.

316
00:22:38,520 --> 00:22:39,880
Okay then.

317
00:22:39,960 --> 00:22:42,560
I'll listen to every word you say.

318
00:22:43,800 --> 00:22:45,600
I'm not gonna overwork

319
00:22:47,280 --> 00:22:48,680
or drink too much coffee anymore.

320
00:25:19,480 --> 00:25:20,920
Well, well, well,

321
00:25:21,000 --> 00:25:22,440
look at him acting all unstoppable

322
00:25:22,520 --> 00:25:24,320
but ending up here.

323
00:25:29,920 --> 00:25:31,440
Qin, please take him to bed.

324
00:25:32,760 --> 00:25:33,760
As for the rest,

325
00:25:33,840 --> 00:25:35,640
I'll handle it.

326
00:25:37,360 --> 00:25:39,000
I'll do it now.

327
00:25:39,080 --> 00:25:40,400
Right, Qin.

328
00:25:40,480 --> 00:25:44,160
Don't tell him
that I asked you to pick him up.

329
00:25:58,640 --> 00:25:59,520
Duang…

330
00:26:01,040 --> 00:26:02,720
Duang, wake up.

331
00:26:12,640 --> 00:26:14,400
Come on, let's go back to my place.

332
00:26:17,040 --> 00:26:18,360
Hey…

333
00:26:18,440 --> 00:26:20,120
just let me help my friends…

334
00:26:20,200 --> 00:26:21,720
You need to rest, Duang.

335
00:26:26,560 --> 00:26:27,840
Just go to bed.

336
00:26:28,640 --> 00:26:30,520
You've been nonstop since yesterday.

337
00:26:38,560 --> 00:26:39,520
But I haven't--

338
00:26:39,600 --> 00:26:40,480
Don't be stubborn.

339
00:26:44,160 --> 00:26:45,440
Qin,

340
00:26:46,480 --> 00:26:48,000
please listen and don't judge.

341
00:26:48,800 --> 00:26:50,520
I don't think Duang's gonna eat that.

342
00:26:51,880 --> 00:26:53,240
I'm hungry.

343
00:26:55,880 --> 00:26:56,800
Go ahead.

344
00:26:56,880 --> 00:26:58,480
Thank you.

345
00:26:58,560 --> 00:27:00,000
Pae, you…

346
00:27:10,480 --> 00:27:11,800
I'm going to go.

347
00:27:23,360 --> 00:27:24,280
Get up.

348
00:27:57,320 --> 00:27:58,760
Your room still smells nice…

349
00:28:13,240 --> 00:28:14,280
Go take a shower.

350
00:29:34,480 --> 00:29:35,960
Pushing yourself to your limits.

351
00:29:36,600 --> 00:29:37,640
How stubborn.

352
00:31:07,080 --> 00:31:08,120
Sheesh!

353
00:31:11,480 --> 00:31:13,800
<i>Returned the storage room key for you.</i>

354
00:31:13,880 --> 00:31:15,480
The work is done?

355
00:31:15,560 --> 00:31:16,640
Isn't that a good thing?

356
00:31:22,680 --> 00:31:24,400
Jamie asked you to pick me up, didn't he?

357
00:31:25,560 --> 00:31:27,480
Go take a shower.
We're going out.

358
00:31:28,440 --> 00:31:29,920
Where are we going?

359
00:31:30,000 --> 00:31:31,200
Are you coming or not?

360
00:31:34,920 --> 00:31:36,120
Wherever you're taking me,

361
00:31:36,200 --> 00:31:38,280
I'll be right there with you!

362
00:31:40,520 --> 00:31:41,440
Good.

363
00:31:43,600 --> 00:31:45,360
When you know you're at your limit,

364
00:31:45,440 --> 00:31:47,440
don't push yourself, all right?

365
00:31:48,320 --> 00:31:49,240
I'm worried about you.

366
00:31:53,920 --> 00:31:55,400
Stawp, Qin!

367
00:31:55,480 --> 00:31:57,800
Don't play with my heart like that.

368
00:32:01,800 --> 00:32:04,400
Go take a shower.
I put out your clothes already.

369
00:32:04,480 --> 00:32:05,960
Sure thing.

370
00:33:15,880 --> 00:33:17,200
Did you bring me to your house?

371
00:33:18,040 --> 00:33:19,600
Is it your house?

372
00:33:21,960 --> 00:33:23,360
What do your parents like?

373
00:33:23,440 --> 00:33:24,640
I didn't prepare at all.

374
00:33:24,720 --> 00:33:26,120
Let alone bring a gift.

375
00:33:26,200 --> 00:33:27,800
Let's go buy something.

376
00:33:27,880 --> 00:33:28,800
Come on.

377
00:33:32,800 --> 00:33:33,960
Are you done?

378
00:33:37,520 --> 00:33:39,720
My parents are just back from abroad.

379
00:33:40,360 --> 00:33:41,360
They're free today,

380
00:33:42,520 --> 00:33:43,720
so I want you to meet them.

381
00:33:47,240 --> 00:33:48,560
Are we going in?

382
00:33:49,880 --> 00:33:50,800
Yes.

383
00:33:51,600 --> 00:33:52,520
Come on.

384
00:34:09,400 --> 00:34:11,120
Qin, are you home?

385
00:34:20,000 --> 00:34:21,320
I brought Duang with me today.

386
00:34:21,400 --> 00:34:23,080
- Hello.
- Hello.

387
00:34:23,679 --> 00:34:25,120
Have you two eaten?

388
00:34:26,440 --> 00:34:28,400
We haven't, ma'am.

389
00:34:28,480 --> 00:34:30,560
No need to call me ma'am.

390
00:34:30,639 --> 00:34:32,120
You can call me Mom, like Qin does.

391
00:34:32,199 --> 00:34:33,159
Of course, Mom!

392
00:34:37,600 --> 00:34:38,520
Right.

393
00:34:38,600 --> 00:34:40,679
Then, let's have a meal together.

394
00:34:40,760 --> 00:34:42,600
Dad even cooked today, Qin.

395
00:34:44,000 --> 00:34:45,040
Right, Mom.

396
00:34:45,760 --> 00:34:47,560
Duang doesn't eat Chinese Kale.

397
00:34:51,239 --> 00:34:53,199
You've told me so many times.

398
00:34:53,280 --> 00:34:54,679
I remember.

399
00:34:55,480 --> 00:34:56,600
Mom.

400
00:34:58,120 --> 00:34:59,400
Come on, let's eat.

401
00:35:04,960 --> 00:35:06,200
You're as pretty as your mom.

402
00:35:06,280 --> 00:35:07,600
Stop.

403
00:35:07,680 --> 00:35:10,520
Well, you really do look like her.

404
00:35:11,080 --> 00:35:12,280
Have you even seen my dad?

405
00:35:12,920 --> 00:35:14,480
Yeah… You're right.

406
00:35:20,240 --> 00:35:22,280
- There you go, honey.
- Thank you.

407
00:35:24,080 --> 00:35:25,000
Duang,

408
00:35:25,560 --> 00:35:26,800
don't be nervous.

409
00:35:27,600 --> 00:35:28,520
All right.

410
00:35:34,360 --> 00:35:36,360
Duang, did you know
that you're the first one?

411
00:35:36,440 --> 00:35:38,400
Qin's never brought anyone home before.

412
00:35:41,640 --> 00:35:43,120
School's just been tough.

413
00:35:43,200 --> 00:35:44,760
That's not true.

414
00:35:44,840 --> 00:35:47,000
If that was the case,
you would've said something.

415
00:35:47,080 --> 00:35:48,320
You're very smart, after all.

416
00:35:48,400 --> 00:35:50,000
I don't believe you.

417
00:36:00,840 --> 00:36:01,680
Qin,

418
00:36:02,600 --> 00:36:03,960
do you like my cooking?

419
00:36:05,440 --> 00:36:06,360
I do.

420
00:36:07,280 --> 00:36:08,200
What about you, Duang?

421
00:36:10,320 --> 00:36:11,960
It's really good. Everything is.

422
00:36:12,040 --> 00:36:13,640
The fish is sweet,

423
00:36:13,720 --> 00:36:14,800
the shrimp are so fresh,

424
00:36:14,880 --> 00:36:16,640
and every cube of ice is nice and cold.

425
00:36:16,720 --> 00:36:17,840
I love everything.

426
00:36:19,480 --> 00:36:20,440
Do you believe it now?

427
00:36:20,520 --> 00:36:21,800
I do now, honey.

428
00:36:22,600 --> 00:36:25,000
Duang, you're a funny guy.

429
00:36:26,160 --> 00:36:27,360
That's nice.

430
00:36:27,440 --> 00:36:29,320
Be the color in Qin's life.

431
00:36:40,840 --> 00:36:42,200
Right, Qin.

432
00:36:42,280 --> 00:36:45,320
Next week,
Mom and I are traveling to San Francisco.

433
00:36:46,280 --> 00:36:47,840
You've been four times already.

434
00:36:48,600 --> 00:36:50,080
Are you buying a house there?

435
00:36:53,440 --> 00:36:56,160
See, sweetie? I told you so.

436
00:36:56,240 --> 00:36:57,480
He's scolding you.

437
00:36:57,560 --> 00:36:59,200
I'm not.

438
00:36:59,280 --> 00:37:00,360
It's just a question.

439
00:37:02,040 --> 00:37:03,720
Well, the city's just my cup of tea.

440
00:37:06,280 --> 00:37:07,160
Have you been, Duang?

441
00:37:07,720 --> 00:37:08,560
I haven't.

442
00:37:08,640 --> 00:37:10,480
We'll take a trip together then.

443
00:37:11,040 --> 00:37:12,520
Come with me, Mom,

444
00:37:12,600 --> 00:37:13,960
and Qin.

445
00:37:14,040 --> 00:37:15,920
Ask for your parents' permission
in advance.

446
00:37:16,000 --> 00:37:17,120
Just come.

447
00:37:17,760 --> 00:37:18,600
All right.

448
00:37:20,360 --> 00:37:21,400
In that case…

449
00:37:21,480 --> 00:37:23,360
give me some notice before the trip.

450
00:37:23,440 --> 00:37:25,160
I don't think I'll be home often.

451
00:37:26,120 --> 00:37:27,880
Sure thing.

452
00:37:34,680 --> 00:37:35,680
Here's a shrimp for you.

453
00:37:43,680 --> 00:37:46,920
I'm happy that
Qin's got you to take care of him, Duang.

454
00:37:50,640 --> 00:37:51,520
Of course.

455
00:37:51,600 --> 00:37:53,120
Me too.

456
00:37:54,160 --> 00:37:56,400
Qin sure looks more lively.

457
00:38:02,400 --> 00:38:05,240
Boys, Mom and I
will go see a movie tonight.

458
00:38:06,960 --> 00:38:07,800
Duang,

459
00:38:08,720 --> 00:38:10,640
can you spend the night here with Qin?

460
00:38:14,920 --> 00:38:18,040
I'm taking her on a romantic date,

461
00:38:18,120 --> 00:38:19,240
and it's a romance movie.

462
00:38:19,320 --> 00:38:21,920
It's probably not Qin's style.

463
00:38:23,080 --> 00:38:24,600
Oh, really?

464
00:38:24,680 --> 00:38:27,240
- But <i>A Star Is Born--</i>
- It's all right.

465
00:38:29,280 --> 00:38:30,680
You two can go.

466
00:38:30,760 --> 00:38:32,120
I'll be fine.

467
00:38:32,600 --> 00:38:33,440
I'm used to it.

468
00:38:35,200 --> 00:38:36,560
Duang, are you okay with that?

469
00:38:36,640 --> 00:38:37,600
Yes.

470
00:38:37,680 --> 00:38:39,520
If it's not a problem, of course.

471
00:38:39,600 --> 00:38:41,160
Not at all.

472
00:38:41,240 --> 00:38:42,480
It's my pleasure, really.

473
00:38:43,640 --> 00:38:45,600
You're like another son of mine, Duang.

474
00:38:46,640 --> 00:38:48,040
Please take care of him for me.

475
00:38:52,920 --> 00:38:53,760
Qin,

476
00:38:53,840 --> 00:38:55,160
after the meal,

477
00:38:55,240 --> 00:38:58,520
can you take a look at my guitar?

478
00:38:58,600 --> 00:39:01,400
I haven't played in ages,
it might be out of tune.

479
00:39:02,440 --> 00:39:03,600
Of course.

480
00:39:17,320 --> 00:39:18,720
What classes are you taking?

481
00:39:20,560 --> 00:39:21,480
Well…

482
00:39:24,080 --> 00:39:25,680
Music stuff.

483
00:39:27,040 --> 00:39:29,440
My friends and I are practicing

484
00:39:29,520 --> 00:39:30,960
for the jazz showcase.

485
00:39:31,760 --> 00:39:32,680
Really?

486
00:39:33,480 --> 00:39:34,840
When is it?

487
00:39:36,280 --> 00:39:37,720
I don't think you'll be here.

488
00:39:37,800 --> 00:39:39,000
Why not?

489
00:39:39,680 --> 00:39:41,320
I might.

490
00:39:41,960 --> 00:39:43,680
I could watch you play jazz.

491
00:39:45,040 --> 00:39:46,480
That sounds quite romantic.

492
00:39:47,920 --> 00:39:49,640
I'll let you know closer to the date.

493
00:39:51,800 --> 00:39:53,840
You wanted me to tune your guitar, right?

494
00:40:08,920 --> 00:40:11,120
You're growing up fast, huh?

495
00:40:13,200 --> 00:40:15,920
Back then,
I was the one tuning your guitar.

496
00:40:20,400 --> 00:40:21,520
You can do it yourself,

497
00:40:21,600 --> 00:40:22,720
so why did you ask me to?

498
00:40:22,800 --> 00:40:25,000
Well, since you've gotten better than me,

499
00:40:25,520 --> 00:40:27,040
I want you to do it.

500
00:40:32,800 --> 00:40:35,280
It's nice that
our family is having a nice moment,

501
00:40:35,360 --> 00:40:36,640
don't you agree?

502
00:40:41,880 --> 00:40:43,040
- Duang?
- Yes?

503
00:40:43,120 --> 00:40:44,960
Do you like dessert?

504
00:40:45,040 --> 00:40:47,160
I do.

505
00:40:47,240 --> 00:40:48,760
I've been eating lots with Qin.

506
00:40:48,840 --> 00:40:50,320
He absolutely loves desserts.

507
00:40:50,400 --> 00:40:52,840
He got that from me.

508
00:40:53,600 --> 00:40:54,920
Really?

509
00:40:56,640 --> 00:40:58,680
I used to buy him lots of desserts,

510
00:40:58,760 --> 00:41:00,080
and when he noms…

511
00:41:02,120 --> 00:41:04,640
I mean, when he eats,

512
00:41:04,720 --> 00:41:06,320
he looks adorable.

513
00:41:14,360 --> 00:41:16,520
I'm glad that you opened up to Duang,

514
00:41:18,520 --> 00:41:20,520
that you have someone new in your life.

515
00:41:26,120 --> 00:41:28,400
Even though you haven't played
for a long time,

516
00:41:28,480 --> 00:41:29,760
it's still working just fine.

517
00:41:37,240 --> 00:41:38,560
I'll go see Duang now.

518
00:41:50,320 --> 00:41:54,320
Qin is quiet and not so good with words.

519
00:41:54,400 --> 00:41:56,480
Please be patient with him.

520
00:41:57,200 --> 00:41:58,320
Of course.

521
00:42:00,400 --> 00:42:02,720
Qin might seem stern,

522
00:42:02,800 --> 00:42:04,200
but he's actually the cutest.

523
00:42:04,280 --> 00:42:06,040
He brings me peace of mind.

524
00:42:08,280 --> 00:42:09,480
Stern…

525
00:42:10,640 --> 00:42:12,480
Did I say something wrong?

526
00:42:12,560 --> 00:42:14,160
No, not at all.

527
00:42:16,400 --> 00:42:18,600
The reason he seems that way
is probably because of…

528
00:42:19,520 --> 00:42:21,160
his dad and me.

529
00:42:24,840 --> 00:42:25,760
Back then,

530
00:42:25,840 --> 00:42:29,800
we made some mistakes.

531
00:42:29,880 --> 00:42:33,040
I guess that's why
he doesn't want to be home with us.

532
00:42:41,480 --> 00:42:42,640
You're annoying!

533
00:42:42,720 --> 00:42:43,840
I told you to shut up!

534
00:42:53,080 --> 00:42:54,280
I thought…

535
00:42:54,360 --> 00:42:57,760
Qin wouldn't remember those things.

536
00:42:58,360 --> 00:43:00,000
But we've never forgotten,

537
00:43:00,840 --> 00:43:03,160
and we've never talked to him about it.

538
00:43:09,480 --> 00:43:10,680
I understand.

539
00:43:11,880 --> 00:43:14,160
Qin has been through a lot.

540
00:43:14,800 --> 00:43:17,000
I only want the best for him.

541
00:43:17,920 --> 00:43:19,840
He's always been strong though.

542
00:43:19,920 --> 00:43:23,920
I sometimes wish
I could be half as strong as him.

543
00:43:28,760 --> 00:43:30,920
I saw him smile today.

544
00:43:31,480 --> 00:43:33,800
It must be because of you.

545
00:43:36,760 --> 00:43:38,480
Please take good care of him for me.

546
00:43:39,560 --> 00:43:40,480
Of course.

547
00:43:40,560 --> 00:43:41,600
That'd be my pleasure.

548
00:43:46,720 --> 00:43:47,560
Orange juice…

549
00:43:48,560 --> 00:43:49,520
Yes, orange juice.

550
00:44:11,800 --> 00:44:14,600
It's snack time, Young Master!

551
00:44:19,640 --> 00:44:20,680
We're leaving now.

552
00:44:20,760 --> 00:44:22,400
Make yourself at home.

553
00:44:22,480 --> 00:44:23,320
Bye-bye.

554
00:44:23,400 --> 00:44:24,360
- Bye.
- Bye now.

555
00:44:27,280 --> 00:44:28,800
- After you, honey.
- Why, thank you.

556
00:45:15,840 --> 00:45:16,680
Duang…

557
00:45:30,440 --> 00:45:31,680
Qin, my lovely.

558
00:45:31,760 --> 00:45:32,920
Then…

559
00:45:33,000 --> 00:45:34,600
I'm gonna look through your photos.

560
00:45:35,960 --> 00:45:36,800
Go ahead.

561
00:45:41,080 --> 00:45:42,360
Who's this?

562
00:45:42,440 --> 00:45:43,560
It's me.

563
00:45:49,800 --> 00:45:51,320
You had long hair back then?

564
00:45:53,200 --> 00:45:54,480
I wanted to be like Tarzan.

565
00:45:57,160 --> 00:45:58,120
Qin,

566
00:45:58,200 --> 00:45:59,440
please.

567
00:46:02,880 --> 00:46:04,080
I wish I were lying.

568
00:46:05,560 --> 00:46:06,880
So adorable.

569
00:46:10,800 --> 00:46:12,080
There.

570
00:46:14,080 --> 00:46:14,960
Hey,

571
00:46:15,680 --> 00:46:17,280
why did you suddenly bring me here?

572
00:46:19,240 --> 00:46:20,920
To me, family is the most important.

573
00:46:22,360 --> 00:46:24,360
I wanted you to meet Dad and Mom,

574
00:46:24,440 --> 00:46:25,760
and I wanted them to meet you.

575
00:46:29,200 --> 00:46:31,480
What's your plan now?

576
00:46:31,560 --> 00:46:32,560
You're getting serious.

577
00:46:33,840 --> 00:46:34,880
I'm not playing around.

578
00:46:36,440 --> 00:46:38,240
I'm not playing around with you either.

579
00:46:38,320 --> 00:46:40,080
Not family, not me,

580
00:46:40,160 --> 00:46:41,080
not anyone.

581
00:46:45,440 --> 00:46:47,400
Yeah, but…

582
00:46:47,480 --> 00:46:48,840
Your family is great.

583
00:46:49,520 --> 00:46:50,800
Your parents are nice.

584
00:46:54,840 --> 00:46:57,440
It's good because you're here.

585
00:47:02,360 --> 00:47:05,000
You're making me blush.

586
00:47:05,080 --> 00:47:07,160
I want to see your bedroom.

587
00:47:07,840 --> 00:47:09,440
Can you take me there?

588
00:47:16,160 --> 00:47:17,120
Dirty mind.

589
00:47:23,400 --> 00:47:24,400
Fine.

590
00:47:25,800 --> 00:47:26,960
Follow me.

591
00:47:31,720 --> 00:47:33,720
I'll definitely ask him this time.

592
00:47:48,840 --> 00:47:50,160
Can you play for me?

593
00:47:52,840 --> 00:47:53,960
Pick a song.

594
00:47:56,120 --> 00:47:58,920
"Ordinary People'" by John Legend.

595
00:47:59,000 --> 00:48:00,960
I heard you humming it before.

596
00:49:25,560 --> 00:49:26,880
Hey.

597
00:49:28,080 --> 00:49:29,000
What?

598
00:49:42,240 --> 00:49:43,120
What is it?

599
00:49:52,240 --> 00:49:53,680
If I don't ask you now,

600
00:49:54,960 --> 00:49:56,360
I'll probably go insane.

601
00:50:06,000 --> 00:50:07,600
- Be my boyfriend?
- Be my boyfriend?

602
00:50:17,440 --> 00:50:18,360
Qin…

603
00:50:20,120 --> 00:50:21,680
You didn't put any effort into it.

604
00:50:21,760 --> 00:50:23,920
You let me play the piano for you,

605
00:50:24,000 --> 00:50:25,280
and then asked me that?

606
00:50:31,920 --> 00:50:33,080
No, wait.

607
00:50:33,160 --> 00:50:34,280
I'm gonna cry.

608
00:50:37,800 --> 00:50:38,960
Not right now.

609
00:50:39,960 --> 00:50:40,960
Answer me.

610
00:50:42,720 --> 00:50:44,720
Will you be my boyfriend, Duang?

611
00:50:51,040 --> 00:50:51,960
I will.

612
00:50:53,520 --> 00:50:54,400
Of course I will.

613
00:51:03,920 --> 00:51:05,320
I'm on cloud nine.

614
00:51:09,360 --> 00:51:11,360
If this is a dream,
then I don't wanna wake up.

615
00:51:12,760 --> 00:51:14,480
I don't even trust myself.

616
00:51:16,280 --> 00:51:19,080
But you made me
trust you with all my heart, Duang.

617
00:52:59,280 --> 00:53:00,480
You probably don't even know

618
00:53:01,560 --> 00:53:03,600
that we've met before.

619
00:53:20,880 --> 00:53:21,760
Pae!

620
00:53:21,840 --> 00:53:22,720
- Pae!
- Jamie!

621
00:53:22,800 --> 00:53:23,840
Jamie!

622
00:53:25,480 --> 00:53:26,600
Pae!

623
00:53:32,040 --> 00:53:32,960
Whoa, don't do it.

624
00:53:34,240 --> 00:53:35,720
<i>You remember me?</i>

625
00:53:35,800 --> 00:53:37,000
<i>I've seen you so many times.</i>

626
00:53:37,080 --> 00:53:38,520
What was that? Whoa!

627
00:53:39,080 --> 00:53:40,240
Why did you do that?

628
00:53:40,800 --> 00:53:41,960
- Wanna have some curry?
- Ow!

629
00:53:42,040 --> 00:53:43,360
What…

630
00:53:44,560 --> 00:53:45,400
What?

631
00:53:46,800 --> 00:53:47,720
Duang!

632
00:53:48,360 --> 00:53:49,280
Thanks.

633
00:53:53,600 --> 00:53:55,320
I take the BTS. What about you?

634
00:53:56,160 --> 00:53:57,840
Motorcycle taxi. I'll walk you.

635
00:54:01,160 --> 00:54:02,520
<i>Did you have a crush on me then?</i>

636
00:54:02,600 --> 00:54:03,680
<i>Like in romantic movies?</i>

637
00:54:04,400 --> 00:54:05,520
<i>You are full of yourself.</i>

638
00:54:07,000 --> 00:54:09,400
<i>I remember you</i>
<i>because your look got on my nerves.</i>

639
00:54:10,680 --> 00:54:11,680
<i>So there's that.</i>

640
00:54:12,400 --> 00:54:13,920
<i>I never knew this before today.</i>

641
00:54:14,000 --> 00:54:15,680
<i>Why didn't you tell me?</i>

642
00:54:15,760 --> 00:54:16,760
<i>I'm telling you now.</i>

643
00:54:23,800 --> 00:54:25,600
Thank you for winning my heart, Duang.

644
00:54:27,880 --> 00:54:30,200
I love you so much
it's like I'm under a spell.

645
00:54:31,760 --> 00:54:32,680
Really now?

646
00:54:36,080 --> 00:54:37,880
I'll be your protector.

647
00:54:39,560 --> 00:54:41,240
No matter what you face,

648
00:54:43,760 --> 00:54:45,640
I'll be there through everything…

649
00:54:48,880 --> 00:54:51,000
through every chapter,

650
00:54:51,080 --> 00:54:52,080
and every place.

651
00:54:53,600 --> 00:54:55,320
It's always gonna be you, Qin.

652
00:54:58,360 --> 00:54:59,840
It's always gonna be you, Duang.

653
00:55:50,240 --> 00:55:51,640
Can I?

654
00:55:51,720 --> 00:55:53,080
You can.

655
00:56:19,520 --> 00:56:20,440
Bastard.

656
00:57:47,520 --> 00:57:48,520
Can you handle it?

657
00:57:52,640 --> 00:57:54,120
Shut your mouth.

658
00:57:54,920 --> 00:57:56,520
Do you really want me to?

659
00:57:59,400 --> 00:58:00,600
Duang…

660
00:58:01,880 --> 00:58:02,800
Yes?

661
00:58:04,280 --> 00:58:05,280
Kiss me.

662
00:58:08,040 --> 00:58:09,200
You're adorable.

663
01:00:47,160 --> 01:00:49,120
Do your best to handle me.

664
01:01:25,760 --> 01:01:29,040
From now on,
I'll devote even more of my love to you.

665
01:01:29,120 --> 01:01:30,760
Me and Qin

666
01:01:30,840 --> 01:01:32,720
- are now boyfriends.
- What did you say?

667
01:01:32,800 --> 01:01:35,440
Surprise!

668
01:01:35,520 --> 01:01:37,600
No care for his friends, whatsoever.

669
01:01:37,680 --> 01:01:39,520
<i>This showcase is serious.</i>

670
01:01:39,600 --> 01:01:41,120
<i>I'm not gonna call.</i>

671
01:01:41,200 --> 01:01:42,080
<i>I need to hang tough.</i>

672
01:01:42,160 --> 01:01:43,520
I'm outside your place.

673
01:01:43,600 --> 01:01:45,400
So you're hooked on me?

674
01:01:45,480 --> 01:01:46,760
You can't disappear like that.

675
01:01:46,840 --> 01:01:48,680
Better watch it though.

676
01:01:48,760 --> 01:01:51,200
I'll devour you the minute you get drunk.

677
01:01:51,280 --> 01:01:52,880
You watch your back.
